<HEADLINE>
URGENT: Obama says U.S. recognizes Tibet as part of China
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BEIJING Nov. 17 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
United States President Barack Obama Tuesday said the U.S. government recognizes
that Tibet is part of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the United States supports the early resumption of dialogue
between the Chinese government and representatives of the Dalai Lama to resolve
any concerns and differences that the two sides may have.
</P>
<P>
"The United States respects the sovereignty and territorial integrity of China,"
Obama said at a joint press conference with Chinese President Hu Jintao at
Beijing's Great Hall of the People.
</P>
</TEXT>
