<HEADLINE>
China, Qatar vow to boost bilateral cooperation in various fields
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
DOHA, Nov. 10 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China and Qatar on Tuesday pledged efforts to boost bilateral cooperation in
various fields and push forward the friendly relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Song Tao, Qatari Crown
Prince Sheikh Tamim Bin Hamad bin Khalifa Al-Thani said Qatar has always
attached great importance to the friendly ties with China.
</P>
<P>
He said Qatar is willing to work together with China to enhance bilateral
cooperation in such fields as economy, energy, culture and education.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Song said China and Qatar have maintained a good momentum in their
friendly relations, featured by frequent high- level visits, enhanced political
trust and comprehensive cooperation in various sectors.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to join hands with Qatar to promote bilateral cooperation in
various fields and bring the friendly ties between the two countries to a new
high, said Song.
</P>
<P>
Song is heading a Chinese delegation to the third session of the Conference of
the State Parties to the United Nations Convention Against Corruption, currently
held in the Qatari capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
