<HEADLINE>
Mexico condemns recent Pakistan series suicide bomb attacks
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
MEXICO CITY, Nov. 10 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Mexican Foreign Ministry strongly condemned on Tuesday a series of suicide
bomb attacks in Pakistan that killed more than 25 people in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
The government of Mexico expressed its concerns and strongly condemned the
series of attacks that took place in Pakistan from Nov. 6 to 10, said a
statement issued by the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
"Mexico expresses its most sincere condolences to the victims' families and to
the people and government of Pakistan," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
A suicide car bomb attack killed at least 20 people in a crowded market place in
northwestern city Charsadda on Tuesday. On Monday a suicide attack killed at
least three people including a policeman in Peshawar. Another suicide bomber
killed 13 people including a local mayor in the city on Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
